CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 8, 1955, pg. 11, reads: "Cotillion Debs - As the time for the Alpha Kappa Alpha's fourth annual cotillion approaches, the young debutantes are becoming more and more excited. Here is a group of lovelies admiring one of the gowns which will be worn. Seated, left to right: Helen Adair and Barbara Mason. Standing, left to right; Barbara Smith, Alfretta Turner and Janyce Murray.  Friday, Feb. 11, is the date, and the Gateway Plaza is the place."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of five Alpha Kappa Alpha debutantes, seated from left: Helen Adair and possibly Barbara Mason; standing: Barbara Smith, Alfretta Turner holding up dress, and Janyce Murray, posed in domestic interior
